<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880108-0100 </DOCNO><HL> Venture of Textron And Boeing Receives Contract From Navy </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TXT BA IBM RTN UTX CSP ROK </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The joint venture of Textron Inc.'s Bell Helicopter Textron unit and Boeing Co.'s Boeing Helicopter Co. unit won a $262.5 million Navy contract to continue development of the V-22 tilt-rotor aircraft.    International Business Machines Corp. got a $43.4 million Air Force contract for electronic equipment for MC-130H aircraft.    Raytheon Co. received a $28.4 million Navy contract for electronic equipment for EA-6B aircraft.    Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., got contracts totaling $21.8 million for UH-60 helicopter production for the Army and spare parts for the Navy.    Combustion Engineering Operations andamp; Maintenance Services Inc., a unit of Combustion Engineering Inc., was issued a $17.1 million Army contract for facilities to make binary chemicals.    Rockwell International Corp. was given a $14 million Navy contract to develop communications equipment for E-6A and E-4 aircraft. </TEXT></DOC>